Definition: a violent commotion or disturbance
Example: the storms that had characterized their relationship had died away; it was only a tempest in a teapot
Synonyms: adj, all, unpeaceful, stormy, verb, stative, tempest, tempestuous, disturbance, a, violent, commotion, or, the, storms, that, had, characterized, their, relationship, died, away, it, was, only, in, teapot
Category: noun.state
